[ TRADITIONAL FRIED (FALLOW) ]
Make dredge from (per 100g chicken)
- 62.5g flour
- potato starch
- 2g cornflour
- 1g MSG
- 1g baking soda
- 2.5g salt
- 0.2g black pepper
- 0.2g white pepper

Make wet dredge from:
- dry dredge
- whole eggs

Make marinade from (per 100g chicken):
- 5g dry dredge
- 0.5g kombu dashi poder (/MSG)
- 4g pun chun (orig: sriracha)
- 2g Dijon mustard (orig: a little bit of yellow american mustard)
- 3g rice wine vinegar
and marinate for 12 hours

Prep & cook:
- Place marinated chicken into dry dredge
- Toss in dry dredge 60 times
- Jolt, turn upside down, jolt again (to dislodge useless bits) 
- Coat in wet dredge and let drain for a sec
- Into another dry dredge and toss another 60 times
- Another round of jolts
- Fry in 180°C oil for 5 mins


[ SCHNITZ / KATSU ]
Season flour, eggs (beaten), and breadcrumbs with:
- salt
- pepper
- italian herbs
- rosemary

Per 100g chicken:
[spice mix]
- 1.5g salt
- 1g msg
- 1g baking soda
- 0.2g black pep
- 0.2g white pep
- 0.5g paprika
- 0.4g italian herbs
- 0.15g rosemary leaves (from approx 0.2g in sprig form, with stem)

[crumb]
- 18g panko

[egg wash]
- 0.4 eggs

[flour]
- 14g flour



Then coat chicken breast bits and fry at 160°C (with probe, 200°C if measuring base heat)
